    <note>Wang(2) Xun [1818] Both he and his wife died in a great epidemic (dayi) in 1138. His sixth generation ancestor, Renhao [3961], served in the administration of the Wuyue kings. His son, Zhengji [3948], was the husband of Lou(2) Shou's [1265] youngest sister. Zhengji's son-in-law, Lou(2) Zong [3622], was either Lou(2) Shou's [1265] son or nephew. Another son-in-law was Zhang(2) Jun's [211] grandson, Zhang(1) Zhongshu [3132]. The daughter married to Zhongshu died young. Wang(2) Zhengji's granddaughter was married to Lou(2) Shou's [1265] grandson or grandnephew, Lou(2) Di [3621]. Zhengji was Guangxi yunpan in 1183 and appointed Huaixi yunpan in 1185. See also documentation for Zhengji and Zhenggong [19876] for more biographical information on Xun. XNYL, 112.7b. Guangdong TZ, 15.13a. Lou Yue, WJ, 99.15b. Ningpo FZ, 17.1081. CBD, 1, 223-4.</note>
